        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: autoscrub accidental dependency lockfile changes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds deterministic autoscrubbing for package lockfile-only PR residue when the PR branch is in the main OpenClaw repository and the workflow token can push the cleanup commit.\n- Restores only changed package lockfiles from the PR base tree using the Git data API, then creates one narrow commit: `Remove dependency lockfile change`.\n- Skips autoscrub for fork PRs instead of attempting an uncertain push, and posts the blocking comment with the exact manual next step.\n- Skips autoscrub when any changed `package.json` modifies `dependencies` or `devDependencies`, because restoring lockfiles could break frozen installs or dependency semantics.\n\n## User-Facing Comments\n\nThis stacked PR adds one new success comment and expands the blocked comment:\n\n- `Dependency lockfile changes were removed`: posted after a successful autoscrub commit, listing restored lockfiles, target branch, and cleanup commit SHA.\n- `Dependency graph changes are blocked`: now explains whether autoscrub was not attempted for a fork branch, skipped because dependency fields changed, or attempted but rejected by GitHub.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-script.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check -- .github/workflows/dependency-change-awareness.yml scripts/github/dependency-change-awareness.mjs test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-script.test.ts`\n",
